1. When triggered on demand, ask the user to provide a company name

2. Search the internet for recruiters and hiring managers at the specified company, identifying their names and email addresses. Extract and compile a list of recruiter emails found.

3. Present the list of recruiters and their email addresses to the user.

4. Ask the user to provide a job description for the role they're interested in.

5. Based on the job description provided and using the Harini_experience_dump.pdf document to generate a short, compelling blurb (3-5 sentences) explaining why the user would be a good fit for that specific role. Include relevant skills, experience alignment, or unique value they bring.

6. Present the generated personalized blurb to the user.

7. Wait for the user to approve the blurb, if user asks for tweaks make them.

8. Now create a draft, don't send it just create a draft with the blurb and add the link to the job in the email draft

9. In the email draft be sure to include the name of the recruiter in the salutation, if you were able to find it

10. Make sure the last line is always, "I'd love to discuss my candidacy further. Looking forward to hearing from you. "

